misconceptions.student_thought_process: The student believes the trip cost is computed by taking (distance ÷ milesPerGallon) × pricePerGallon, and that writing y/n*z will evaluate in that intended order.
misconceptions.conceptual_gap: In Java, / and * have the same precedence and are evaluated left-to-right, so y/n*z is exactly (y/n)*z. This matches the intended formula, so there is no conceptual gap affecting correctness here.
misconceptions.error_manifestation: No error; output matches the required calculation for the sample inputs (prints 34.297872340425535).
